EARLY this season, GladAfrica Group were announced as the new title sponsors for the Premier Soccer League (PSL) First Division. The league which is currently lead by Ajax Cape Town was subsequently renamed to GladAfrica Championship. GladAfrica agreed to a five-year partnership which was received with great excitement as they also increased the prizes for the teams that finish at the top of the Championship. A year later, as the season is edging closer to the wire with the inaugural champions set to be crowned, GladAfrica Group launched the trophy that would be handed over to the 2019-20 champions. The trophy was revealed on Wednesday night by Premier Soccer League chairman Dr Irvin Khoza alongside GladAfrica Group Executive chairman Noel Mashaba. Mashaba said they spent a significant amount of time trying to figure out symbol that would best represent their commitment to the beautiful sport. "Since entering into this partnership with the PSL, we have  that is so much loved the world over. We wanted a product that embodies the values and traditions of GladAfrica. "From the initial draft design, we moved from one amendment to another until such time that we were satisfied with what we saw with our eyes. It was an involved and often taxing process." The title was forged by 10 artisans, over 150 hours, using a combination of traditional skills and leading design technology according to Mashaba. Khoza said: “This partnership between the PSL and GladAfrica is an exciting relationship because it celebrates the African story of excellence. "We must thank GladAfrica for being part of our family. We know they are strong in engineering services and you can see that this new trophy is as a result of attention to detail. It is something to be proud of. "This current season in the GladAfrica Championship has been very exciting and unpredictable and this has always been the strength of our League.” The GladAfrica trophy will be handed over to the 2019-20 GladAfrica Championship winners on 30 August.